raw_data.title: Associate Engineer/Scientist/Specialist
raw_data.description: Under direct supervision, the Associate Engineer/Scientist/Specialist: Assists in providing analysis, guidance, and insight into the engineering, scientific, or technical discipline under evaluation; Applies fundamentals to solve well-defined problems and seeks assistance when needed; May serve as a project administrator, responsible for assisting in the preparation of budgets, schedules, and project program reports.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Education and experience may be substituted for each other. Each year of relevant experience may be substituted for one year of education, and vice versa as follows: A Bachelors degree is equivelant to a Associate's degree with 4 years of experience and a High School diploma with 10 years of experience. A Masters degree is equivelant to a Bachelor's degree with 2 years of experience and there is no equivalence allowed below a Bachelor's degree.  A Doctorate is equivelant to a Master's degree with 2 years of experience, a Bachelor's degree with 4 years of experience, and there is no equivalence allowed below a Bachelor's degree.

raw_data.title: Principal Engineer/Scientist/Specialist
raw_data.description: In addition to responsibilities of Senior Engineer/Scientist/Specialist II, the Principal Engineer/Scientist/Specialist: Provides technical leadership and advises teams in various areas of expertise; Serves as technical expert (principal investigator) on projects; Manages projects in technical area of expertise that may require multidisciplinary involvement from staff in more than one technical group and/or the use of subcontractors/consultants; Directs the technical activities of individuals and groups; Directs preparation of reports; Deals regularly with top level in client organizations; Directs the activities of individuals and groups toward the end-to-end accomplishment of meaningful goals; Encourages a team effort through training and leadership; Develops and assists in delivery of training programs for staff. The Principal Engineer/Scientist/Specialist will spend the majority of their time performing technical leadership activities or responsibilities, and may also serve in other senior-level administrative roles.
